# CODEOWNERS — process-level defense for credential discipline.
#
# The credential crate holds the 4 policed types (SealedCredential,
# OAuthToken, OAuthRefreshToken, AgentBearerToken) whose trait discipline
# is enforced by `cargo xtask validate-credentials` AND by
# `static_assertions::assert_not_impl_any!` blocks. The orphan rule does NOT
# prevent the defining crate from writing `impl Serialize for OAuthToken`,
# so PRs touching this crate need human review beyond the automated gates.
#
# Every PR touching these paths must be approved by a credential-security
# reviewer (listed below). Maintainers — add GitHub usernames when
# onboarding.

# Credential types and their discipline gates
/crates/permitlayer-credential/**   @botsdown
/xtask/src/validate_credentials/**  @botsdown

# Deny.toml dependency-direction bans — removing an edge here removes a
# compile-time architectural guarantee.
/deny.toml                          @botsdown

# Workspace-level dependency/lint policy
/Cargo.toml                         @botsdown
/rust-toolchain.toml                @botsdown

# `.github/` — protect CODEOWNERS itself, CI workflows, and repo governance.
# A PR that could weaken review requirements must itself be reviewed.
/.github/                           @botsdown
